{{Infobox hospital | Name = Calvary Wakefield Hospital | Org/Group = [[Little Company of Mary Health Care (Australia)|Little Company of Mary Health Care]] | Logo = <!-- optional --> | Location = [[Wakefield Street]] | Region = Adelaide | State = South Australia | Country = Australia | Coordinates = {{coord|-34.9276|138.6113|display=inline,title|region:AU-SA_type:landmark}} | HealthCare = Private, Non-For Profit | Type = General | Speciality = [[Cardiac]], [[Neurosurgery]] and [[Orthopaedics]] | Standards = <!-- optional if no national standards --> | Emergency = Yes | Affiliation = | Beds = 180 | Founded = 1883 | Closed = <!-- optional --> | Website = http://www.calvarywakefield.org.au | Wiki-Links = <!-- optional --> }}
'''Calvary Wakefield Hospital''' (previously '''Wakefield Hospital''') is a private [[Roman Catholic|Catholic]] hospital founded in 1883 in [[Adelaide, Australia]].<ref name="selfabout">{{Cite web |url=http://www.calvarywakefield.org.au/about.html |title=About Calvary Wakefield Hospital |publisher=Little Company of Mary Health Care |accessdate=18 May 2016}}</ref> It provides [[acute care]] with [[Inpatient#Outpatients and inpatients|inpatient and outpatient]] facilities. It also provides [[dentistry|dental care]] and [[plastic surgery|plastic]] and [[reconstructive surgery]] to patients. It is one of four private hospitals in South Australia under the Calvary name.
Since its 2006 acquisition from [[Ramsay Health Care]], the hospital has been one of the Little Company of Mary (LCM) Health Care providers overseen by the international [[religious institute]] [[Sisters of the Little Company of Mary]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cathnews.com/news/605/166.php |title=Calvary completes Adelaide hospital acquisitions |publisher=Catholic News |date=29 May 2006 |accessdate=2008-12-08 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070203204040/http://www.cathnews.com/news/605/166.php |archivedate=February 3, 2007 }}</ref> Prior to its acquisition, the 180-bed hospital was called Wakefield Hospital.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://cathnews.com/news/603/doc/28lcmb.pdf |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160303203427/http://cathnews.com/news/603/doc/28lcmb.pdf |dead-url=yes |archive-date=3 March 2016 |title=Adelaide hospitals acquired by LCM Health Care/Calvary Health Care Adelaide |publisher=Catholic News |accessdate=8 December 2008}} </ref> According to LCM Health Care, it "is the oldest private hospital in South Australia."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.lcmhealthcare.org.au/servicesmap.php?page=/servicesmappages/wakefield |title=Calvary Wakefield Hospital |publisher=Little Company of Mary Health Care |accessdate=8 December 2008}}</ref>
Little Company of Mary Health Care (Australia) is developing a replacement for Calvary Wakefield Hospital through Commercial & General developers and [[John Holland Group|John Holland]] construction. The new hospital in [[Angas Street, Adelaide]], will be next to the [[South Australia Police]] headquarters, and is due to open in early 2019 with 250+ beds, a 220-space carpark and a 350-space carpark developed by Commercial & General nearby.<ref>[http://www.adelaidenow.com.au/news/south-australia/work-to-start-on-300-million-new-calvary-city-hospital-to-replace-wakefield/news-story/cf7658279c7fe7718978dc1c4cd67b23 Paul Starick, (28 May 2016), Work to start on $300 million new Calvary city hospital to replace Wakefield, ''Sunday Mail'' (SA)]. Retrieved 26 April 2017</ref> In August 2018, the new Calvary Hospital Adelaide celebrated its "topping out" ceremony.
