{{unreferenced|date=June 2013}} {{Infobox organization | name = Singapore Cancer Society | logo = | founded_date = 1964 | location = [[Singapore]] | key_people = Mr Wee Leong How, [[Chairman]] and Dr Ravindran Kanesvaran, [[Vice Chairman]], Albert Ching, [[CEO]] | area_served = [[Singapore]] | focus = "To be the leading charitable cancer organisation in Singapore and the region, with a reputation for effective programmes for the prevention and control of cancer." | homepage = http://www.singaporecancersociety.org.sg/ }}
'''The [http://www.singaporecancersociety.org.sg Singapore Cancer Society] (SCS)''', founded in 1964, is the largest cancer advocacy and support organisation in [[Singapore]].
== History == Established in 1964, Singapore Cancer Society is a self-funded voluntary welfare organisation which is dedicated to minimising the impact of cancer in Singapore through the provision of cancer treatment subsidies, financial and welfare aid to needy cancer patients, home hospice care services for terminally-ill cancer patients, as well as rehabilitation support programmes for recovering cancer patients and cancer survivors . In addition, the Society also provides free cancer screening services and promotes cancer awareness and prevention through its public education and community outreach programmes. Annually, the SCS helps more than 1,000 needy cancer patients and reaches out to more than 50,000 individuals through its cancer screening, public educational and community outreach programmes.
