{{Infobox university |name = School of Pharmacy |image = Magnuson_HSB_I_J_Wing.jpg |image_size = 200px |caption = Classes and offices are mostly located within the [[Warren G. Magnuson Health Sciences Building]] |established = 1894<ref>{{cite book |last1=Wills |first1=Antoinette |last2=Bolcer |first2=John D. |date=August 4, 2014 |title=University of Washington |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Dor_AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA7 |location=Charleston, South Carolina |publisher=[[Arcadia Publishing]] |page=7 |isbn=978-1-467-13182-7 |accessdate=December 24, 2017}}</ref> |selectivity = Selective |type = [[Public university|Public]] |dean = Sean D. Sullivan |city = [[Seattle]] |state = [[Washington (state)|Washington]] |country = US |postgrad = |website = {{url|http://sop.washington.edu/}} }}
The '''University of Washington School of Pharmacy''' was founded in 1894 and is one of two [[PharmD]] granting institutions within the state of [[Washington (state)|Washington]]. Offices are located within the [[Warren G. Magnuson Health Sciences Building]] on the [[University of Washington]] campus. [[U.S. News & World Report]] ranked the School of Pharmacy as tied for the tenth best pharmacy school in the United States in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://grad-schools.usnews.rankingsandreviews.com/best-graduate-schools/top-health-schools/pharmacy-rankings |publisher=US News & World Report |title=Best Grad Schools- Pharmacy}}</ref>
Sean Sullivan became the 9th dean of the school in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Balta|first1=Victor|title=Sean D. Sullivan named dean of UW School of Pharmacy|url=http://www.washington.edu/news/2014/07/21/sean-d-sullivan-named-dean-of-uw-school-of-pharmacy/|website=UW Today|publisher=University of Washington|accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=History of the School|url=http://sop.washington.edu/about/history/|website=University of Washington School of Pharmacy|publisher=University of Washington School of Pharmacy|accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref>
As of 2015, the school has 381 [[PharmD]] students, 59 [[PhD]] students, and 40 [[Master of Science|Masters of Science]] students and is 64% female.<ref>{{cite web|title=About Us|url=http://sop.washington.edu/about/|website=University of Washington School of Pharmacy|publisher=University of Washington School of Pharmacy|accessdate=15 February 2015}}</ref>
